&lt;snip&gt;
In fact - how would you implement a Web application without descting
the URI to dispatch to the corresponding resource handler and to serve
up the right representation?
&lt;/snip&gt;

And this is where I think some folks get confused. Since most folks
spend time building _servers_ they get used to the notion that the URI
is laden with important information, they focus on the importance of
constructing &quot;pretty&quot; URIs, etc. Then, when talking here about these
details, there is a wave of &quot;oh, but URIs should be treated as
opaque&quot;, etc.

It is for this reason that, when I talk about URIs in the context of
REST/HTTP, I use the phrase &quot;clients and intermediaries should treat
the URIs constructed by servers as opaque identifiers.&quot;

mca
